summary:
My passion for Psychology can be traced back to my teenage days, when my parents asked me what I wanted to be when I grow up I would always say "I want to be a successful psychologist!". Whether as a member of study groups, always reading about it or even as a supporter to my friends, relatives, and clients. And this is all because I just love being able to impact people's lives and show the practical side of Psychology. Right now I am probably doing some research about a random topic in Psychology! Believe me.

Outside of the office, I'm committed to education and online training. I’m fluent in Portuguese and English, doing my best to become fluent in German and Dutch. I love outdoor activities such as Running, Jogging, Tracking, Cycling or simply staying in the park to enjoy the sun.
